Commits.Comment:
Fix ARC setup and release versioning from not showing package names.

At the moment, if a value is change to TinyType, it converts blank strings to null. This is _mostly_ fine in most places, but a blank package name is used to communicate that a package is the default package, so it's not fine in that place. This caused an issue on the triggers page where some UI elements couldn't get the package and step name based on the id, because it was comparing the "" in the package name list to null on the settings (and not finding a value).

This change converts nulls to "" before doing a comparison, making the lookups work again.
